      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_TenantChargeDelete",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to delete records from two tables: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "TenantChargeDetail",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "TenantCharge",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", both of which reside in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "input",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema. The procedure takes an identifier for a tenant charge and removes the associated records from these tables. This operation is typically used to maintain data integrity by ensuring that detailed records are removed before or alongside their parent records."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving only two "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "DELETE",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " operations. It does not include any conditional logic, loops, or complex transactions, which keeps its complexity low."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
